dct_title_s: Route followed by British expedition 1903-1904 from base at Siiliguri, Darjiling, Nathang Jelep Pass (Jelep La), Yatung, Chumbi, Phari Jong, Tuna Guru, Khang Ma, Gyangtse Jong, Kharo La
dct_description_sm: Map of northern India, Sikkim, Bhutan and Tibet, showing the route of the British expedition of 1903-1904. Relief shown by spot heights. "Traced in Military Information Division, General Staff, Manila, P.I. June 1904. From Edward Stanford's map of part of Tibet."
dct_publisher_sm: Manila, P.I. : Military Information Division, General Staff, 1904.
